WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:07.001
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

00:08.198 --> 00:12.035
- ♪♪ (drumroll, cymbal crash)
- (crowd laughing)

00:18.476 --> 00:20.945
(crowd gasping, applauding)

00:45.970 --> 00:48.604
Told any good lies lately?

00:48.606 --> 00:50.705
Lying is a part of human nature.

00:50.707 --> 00:52.675
We all tell lies.

00:52.677 --> 00:54.876
And those of you who don't

00:54.878 --> 00:57.679
are lying.

00:57.681 --> 01:01.316
Who wants to play? Who wants to play?

01:01.318 --> 01:03.586
You can't win if you're not in.

01:03.588 --> 01:05.420
MAN (narrating): <i>This
one's a classic...</i>

01:05.422 --> 01:07.890
<i>one of the oldest street
swindles in the world...</i>

01:07.892 --> 01:09.857
<i>the three-card monte.</i>

01:09.859 --> 01:12.560
Find the lady. Toss the broad.

01:12.562 --> 01:14.964
The lady in red will get you ahead.

01:14.966 --> 01:18.399
The jokers black will set you back.

01:18.401 --> 01:20.869
MAN (narrating): <i>See
if you can do it.</i>

01:20.871 --> 01:23.274
<i>Keep your eye on the queen.</i>

01:31.381 --> 01:32.447
(laughing)

01:32.449 --> 01:35.651
Ten-to-one. "Ten-to-one,"
the man says.

01:35.653 --> 01:37.753
Those are the odds and not the time,

01:37.755 --> 01:39.622
unless it's time to play!

01:39.624 --> 01:43.658
MAN (narrating): <i>Let me
introduce the Professor.</i>

01:43.660 --> 01:45.593
<i>The beauty of the three-card monte</i>

01:45.595 --> 01:47.863
<i>is that even though
people know it's a scam,</i>

01:47.865 --> 01:49.598
<i>they still play.</i>

01:49.600 --> 01:52.803
<i>Everybody wants to beat the man.</i>

01:53.970 --> 01:56.905
<i>In fact, no sucker will ever
win the three-card monte.</i>

01:56.907 --> 01:59.908
CROWD: Ooh!

01:59.910 --> 02:03.745
- (cheering)
- <i>Unless he's in on the game.</i>

02:03.747 --> 02:06.048
<i>Yep, that's me.</i>

02:06.050 --> 02:07.816
<i>And I'm no sucker.</i>

02:07.818 --> 02:11.753
- Three-card monte's the name of the game.
- (cheering)

02:11.755 --> 02:13.822
<i>A few years ago, I
learnt to tell lies</i>

02:13.824 --> 02:15.958
<i>for profit and pleasure.</i>

02:15.960 --> 02:19.828
<i>You would probably call
me a con man, a swindler.</i>

02:19.830 --> 02:21.629
<i>I prefer the term</i>

02:21.631 --> 02:24.333
<i>"professional liar."</i>

02:24.335 --> 02:26.067
<i>So let me tell you the truth.</i>

02:26.069 --> 02:28.772
<i>Come on, trust me.</i>

02:41.718 --> 02:44.120
MAN: And start.

02:53.764 --> 02:56.031
MAN (narrating): <i>You
recognize this scene, right?</i>

02:56.033 --> 02:58.434
<i>Final maths exam.</i>

02:58.436 --> 03:00.902
<i>Chinese kid.</i>

03:00.904 --> 03:05.373
<i>Nervous, but he's
totally gonna ace it.</i>

03:05.375 --> 03:10.113
<i>Well, you'd be right if
you were talking about</i> him.

03:13.850 --> 03:17.051
<i>But we're talking about me,</i>

03:17.053 --> 03:19.422
<i>the good-looking one.</i>

03:40.044 --> 03:42.011
Aaah!

03:53.824 --> 03:55.890
It's all fun and games, Master Lawrence,

03:55.892 --> 03:57.893
until someone loses an eye.

03:57.895 --> 04:00.128
Can my son still sit the exam?

04:00.130 --> 04:02.563
Lawrence has brought
great shame to the school.

04:02.565 --> 04:05.434
There's also the injury to
young Jeremy Fong to consider.

04:05.436 --> 04:07.703
But no exam means no university.

04:07.705 --> 04:11.673
I'm afraid Lawrence must
suffer the maximum penalty.

04:11.675 --> 04:13.542
Lawrence?

04:13.544 --> 04:15.777
There are no short cuts.

04:15.779 --> 04:18.781
Cheating will never get you anywhere.

04:20.784 --> 04:23.719
But, Mum, everyone's
going. There'll be girls.

04:23.721 --> 04:27.022
- You're not going to Schooler Paradise.
- Surfer's Paradise.

04:27.024 --> 04:29.123
You promised us you studied.

04:29.125 --> 04:32.594
- You lied to your family.
- Our entire family is full of doctors.

04:32.596 --> 04:34.298
Don't we have enough?

04:35.565 --> 04:38.066
- What are you going to be then, huh?
- I don't know.

04:38.068 --> 04:42.470
My sister in China has bought a
ticket to come to your graduation.

04:42.472 --> 04:45.873
- What am I going to tell her?
- You can tell her about Schooler's Paradise.

04:45.875 --> 04:49.212
(speaking Chinese)

05:03.993 --> 05:06.628
Fine! I'll pay you back.

05:06.630 --> 05:09.166
Every last cent.

05:15.039 --> 05:17.205
LAWRENCE (narrating):
<i>What did they expect?</i>

05:17.207 --> 05:19.508
<i>The average person
lies six times a day.</i>

05:19.510 --> 05:22.643
<i>And I only cheated that one time.</i>

05:22.645 --> 05:25.847
<i>I guess you gotta start somewhere.</i>

05:25.849 --> 05:28.684
(man chattering)

05:28.686 --> 05:31.085
- What the hell!
- You want a phone, you need a job.

05:31.087 --> 05:34.890
You want a job, you need an education.

05:34.892 --> 05:38.996
- (bell chiming)
- <i>(woman on PA, indistinct)</i>

05:41.130 --> 05:44.866
- Chinese lucky money?
- Call as soon as you get there.

05:44.868 --> 05:46.835
With what?

05:46.837 --> 05:49.240
Try to be a good boy.

05:55.746 --> 05:58.414
(Chinese)

06:12.061 --> 06:15.864
Look at these monkeys. They think
they get something for nothing.

06:15.866 --> 06:19.436
But they're just idiots for us to laugh at.

06:29.847 --> 06:32.080
You need to work hard for what you want.

06:32.082 --> 06:35.052
Life is not a game show.

06:37.887 --> 06:42.090
Lawrence, just because your father
sent you here as a punishment

06:42.092 --> 06:44.092
does not mean you cannot have fun.

06:44.094 --> 06:46.929
I can put on my computer
for you to play on.

06:46.931 --> 06:49.965
- Do you have a modem?
- No, Lawrence.

06:49.967 --> 06:52.169
A Macintosh.

06:57.941 --> 06:59.943
(button clicks)

07:03.780 --> 07:05.647
LAWRENCE (narrating):
<i>Uncle Sam loved chess.</i>

07:05.649 --> 07:08.116
<i>I mean, really loved it.</i>

07:08.118 --> 07:11.152
<i>Chess taught him everything
that was important in life...</i>

07:11.154 --> 07:15.491
<i>discipline, tradition,
self-control.</i>

07:17.695 --> 07:20.027
<i>I want to die.</i>

07:20.029 --> 07:23.032
(clocks ticking)

07:36.613 --> 07:40.681
Lawrence, Soo Jin is our club champion.

07:40.683 --> 07:42.818
Lawrence is very smart.

07:42.820 --> 07:45.720
Make a good Chinese boyfriend. (chuckles)

07:45.722 --> 07:48.390
I will leave you two kids together.

07:48.392 --> 07:52.126
I'm sure you'll have lots to talk about.

07:52.128 --> 07:56.765
- She's eight.
- No, Soo Jin is 10, and I'm 52.

07:56.767 --> 07:59.267
Anyone who can beat your
uncle in a game of chess

07:59.269 --> 08:03.073
must have something worthwhile to say.

08:07.811 --> 08:10.111
(loud clattering)

08:10.113 --> 08:14.417
(chuckling) That's the spirit.

08:16.120 --> 08:17.785
Excuse me, sir.

08:17.787 --> 08:20.888
If you're not here to play chess,
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

08:20.890 --> 08:24.225
My good man, I am here to play.

08:24.227 --> 08:26.328
A visitor's game is five dollars.

08:26.330 --> 08:27.962
(chuckling)

08:27.964 --> 08:31.667
Who's the president of
this fine establishment?

08:31.669 --> 08:34.301
- I am.
- Oh, excellent.

08:34.303 --> 08:37.304
You're a man of chess, no less.

08:37.307 --> 08:39.974
A yellow Kasparov. (chuckling)

08:39.976 --> 08:42.309
I, too, am quite the master

08:42.312 --> 08:46.047
even if I do say so myself, which I do!

08:46.049 --> 08:49.051
I've not been beaten for nine years.

08:49.053 --> 08:51.753
This is a tragedy, but
I've come all the way...

08:51.755 --> 08:54.955
to the antipodes for a new challenge.

08:54.957 --> 08:59.161
Mr. President, I propose to you a wager.

08:59.163 --> 09:02.263
Defeat me in a single game,

09:02.265 --> 09:06.868
and you can ram-jam
ramabam these 50 clams...

09:06.870 --> 09:08.970
into your old skyrocket.

09:08.972 --> 09:10.705
I don't play for money.

09:10.707 --> 09:14.042
Oh! (mutters)

09:14.044 --> 09:17.378
(chuckles) So who is the
best player in the club?

09:17.380 --> 09:19.181
- Me!
- Ah!

09:19.183 --> 09:22.050
I won the club championship three times.

09:22.052 --> 09:24.720
Oh, my.

09:24.722 --> 09:26.922
Delighted to meet you, young lady.

09:26.924 --> 09:29.559
Enough!

09:32.361 --> 09:36.031
In that case, I shall defeat you all.

09:36.033 --> 09:38.166
This is a serious club.

09:38.168 --> 09:41.836
Very well. I shall defeat
at least half of you.

09:41.838 --> 09:44.105
Gentlemen... and young lady...

09:44.107 --> 09:47.209
the terms of tonight's wager.

09:47.211 --> 09:49.244
I shall play you, Chairman Mao.

09:49.246 --> 09:51.278
In fact, I shall play you all.

09:51.280 --> 09:55.282
I stake my money that A:
I will defeat you, sir,

09:55.284 --> 09:58.253
B: I will defeat at least half of you,

09:58.255 --> 10:00.321
and C:

10:00.323 --> 10:06.262
I will play you all at
exactly the same time!

10:42.533 --> 10:44.701
Hmm.

10:54.911 --> 10:57.180
Hmm. Well.

11:33.449 --> 11:35.883
(grunts)

11:35.885 --> 11:38.722
Checkmate. Yes!

11:44.260 --> 11:47.396
(grunting)

12:04.981 --> 12:10.886
Gentlemen, thank you for
being so gracious in defeat.

12:10.888 --> 12:13.654
But ruminate on this.

12:13.656 --> 12:18.058
Next time, I might play sober.

12:18.060 --> 12:21.930
- (chuckling)
- (murmuring)

12:21.932 --> 12:24.065
SOO JIN: He's brilliant.

12:24.067 --> 12:27.371
Yeah. Very clever.

12:37.514 --> 12:41.649
Why would you be following
an old drunk down an alley?

12:41.651 --> 12:45.152
I'm a good judge of character, young man,

12:45.154 --> 12:48.956
and you don't look like a ruffian to me.

12:48.958 --> 12:51.426
- You forgot something.
- Ah, my whiskey!

12:51.428 --> 12:54.095
Thank you.

12:54.097 --> 12:57.998
Your cold tea.

12:58.000 --> 12:59.700
A harmless little deception

12:59.702 --> 13:02.470
in order to lower the
expectations of one's adversaries.

13:02.472 --> 13:05.005
You're very perceptive for a
young man who doesn't play chess.

13:05.007 --> 13:06.574
Neither do you.

13:06.576 --> 13:09.109
But you just saw me play 10 games at once.

13:09.111 --> 13:10.979
I'm the grand pooh-bah.

13:10.981 --> 13:12.947
I haven't lost a match in 12 years.

13:12.949 --> 13:15.617
- Nine years.
- Well, time flies when you're having fun.

13:15.619 --> 13:19.589
You didn't win 10 games. You
didn't win any games at all.

13:22.491 --> 13:24.725
<i>You played them against each other.</i>

13:24.727 --> 13:27.162
<i>You watched the move one
player made against you...</i>

13:27.164 --> 13:30.598
<i>and copied it on the opposite board.</i>

13:30.600 --> 13:34.402
<i>Of course you would
win half the games.</i>

13:34.404 --> 13:37.037
<i>And you beat my uncle</i>

13:37.039 --> 13:39.574
<i>because you played him
against the club champion.</i>

13:39.576 --> 13:43.345
Checkmate. Yes!

13:43.347 --> 13:46.715
(laughing)

13:46.717 --> 13:49.584
Lawrence, isn't it?

13:49.586 --> 13:52.186
Well, Lawrence, you've busted my gaffe.

13:52.188 --> 13:55.156
You're Joe hep. You're hep to the game.

13:55.158 --> 13:59.730
And your keen eye has earned
you a pineapple here tonight.

14:01.331 --> 14:04.032
Would you mind?

14:04.034 --> 14:06.401
So you walk in, steal their money

14:06.403 --> 14:08.168
and walk away just like that?

14:08.170 --> 14:11.672
Lawrence, that hurts.

14:11.674 --> 14:15.509
I didn't break any of the
Ten Commandments tonight.

14:15.511 --> 14:17.644
I didn't murder anybody.

14:17.646 --> 14:20.581
I didn't covet my neighbor's donkey,

14:20.583 --> 14:24.418
and I certainly didn't steal anything.

14:24.420 --> 14:27.755
You've just insulted an
old man who gave you $50.

14:27.757 --> 14:29.556
My uncle's $50.

14:29.558 --> 14:32.326
The lure of easy money...

14:32.328 --> 14:35.129
clouds rational thought.

14:35.131 --> 14:37.165
You cannot cheat an honest man.

14:37.167 --> 14:39.133
That is the first rule of my occupation.

14:39.135 --> 14:40.701
A con man.

14:40.703 --> 14:46.041
I prefer the term "professional liar."

14:46.043 --> 14:48.375
- SAM: Lawrence!
- I should go... Wait!

14:48.377 --> 14:50.512
- My money.
- Easy come, easy go.

14:50.514 --> 14:54.081
That also tends to be something of a rule.

14:54.083 --> 14:55.716
I need that money.

14:55.718 --> 15:01.790
If you want to earn it back,
Sunday morning at the mall.

15:01.792 --> 15:04.895
Good evening, <i>Lawrence.</i>

15:25.115 --> 15:27.484
Come on, mate.

15:38.761 --> 15:40.862
Good morning.

15:40.864 --> 15:42.629
Good morning, young man.

15:42.631 --> 15:45.332
It's Lawrence.

15:45.334 --> 15:47.167
What are you doing here?

15:47.169 --> 15:49.470
You said you might need a hand.

15:49.472 --> 15:51.505
What kind of hand?

15:51.507 --> 15:53.675
With whatever scam you've got going on.

15:53.677 --> 15:56.110
Do you think you might
like to speak up a little?

15:56.112 --> 15:59.082
I don't think everybody quite heard you.

16:00.483 --> 16:04.219
Look about you. What do you see, hmm?

16:04.221 --> 16:05.753
Magazines.

16:05.755 --> 16:08.422
For every imaginable interest,

16:08.424 --> 16:10.859
but they're all concerned with desire.

16:10.861 --> 16:14.029
People want what they can't have.

16:15.465 --> 16:19.200
Some are more obviously
concerned with desire.

16:19.202 --> 16:21.702
Persuasion is about giving
people what they want.

16:21.704 --> 16:26.541
- I don't want this.
- Perhaps not, Master Lawrence.

16:26.543 --> 16:28.645
But ask yourself this.

16:32.381 --> 16:35.383
(muttering) Turn around.

16:35.385 --> 16:39.523
- What do you want, hmm?
- (writing)

16:46.795 --> 16:48.797
Thank you.

16:52.769 --> 16:55.603
- My wife is seven months pregnant.
- Excuse me?

16:55.605 --> 16:57.672
A long-time customer
of this establishment.

16:57.674 --> 16:59.641
A subscriber to many fine magazines.

16:59.643 --> 17:01.643
I'm sorry. What was her name?

17:01.645 --> 17:04.744
- And you send her this.
- Oh. Dear.

17:04.747 --> 17:07.781
Perhaps we could just exchange
it for the correct publication.

17:07.784 --> 17:10.584
Yes, of course. I do apologize.

17:10.586 --> 17:12.587
- No, no, no.
- If there's anything I can do.

17:12.589 --> 17:13.921
Not at all.

17:13.923 --> 17:15.490
However... (chuckling)

17:15.492 --> 17:18.525
she's always complaining about the
lack of a good pair of scissors.

17:18.527 --> 17:21.596
Ah. How much for your very best pair?

17:21.598 --> 17:23.599
Oh, please.

17:24.967 --> 17:27.635
It would be my pleasure, sir.

17:27.637 --> 17:29.870
Oh, that is too kind.

17:29.872 --> 17:32.641
Thank you. Good day.

17:34.977 --> 17:38.312
Confidence is about trust.

17:38.314 --> 17:40.747
- Can I borrow $50?
- You already have my 50.

17:40.749 --> 17:44.186
Hmm, I suppose you might see it that way.

17:46.389 --> 17:49.256
Do you really think you've
got what it takes, hmm?

17:49.258 --> 17:51.126
Sure.

17:55.398 --> 17:59.399
Convince her to take the money.

17:59.401 --> 18:01.336
- My $50?
- Yep.

18:01.338 --> 18:04.741
But you have to keep the wallet.

18:11.915 --> 18:13.947
Oh, sorry. Is that your wallet?

18:13.949 --> 18:16.350
Um, no. Is it yours?

18:16.352 --> 18:18.485
- No, it's a man's wallet.
- Yes, um...

18:18.487 --> 18:21.321
- Anyway, do you want the money?
- What? No.

18:21.323 --> 18:24.259
I mean, I just thought I'd keep the
wallet, and you could have the...

18:24.261 --> 18:25.760
Here.

18:25.762 --> 18:28.562
See if there's any ID in it.

18:28.564 --> 18:31.398
- Look, a family man.
- Oh, and $50.

18:31.400 --> 18:33.868
- Don't you want it?
- No. Isn't there, like, a card or something?

18:33.870 --> 18:37.804
No. Wait.

18:37.806 --> 18:39.907
All right.

18:39.909 --> 18:42.377
- (change drops)
- <i>(line rings)</i>

18:42.379 --> 18:43.844
Hello. Is this...

18:43.846 --> 18:45.913
Yes, speaking.

18:45.915 --> 18:49.684
Oh, really? Oh, thank goodness.

18:49.686 --> 18:52.887
What is your name?
Sarah. Oh, that's lovely.

18:52.889 --> 18:55.555
(chuckles) Yes, I have
a daughter called Sarah.

18:55.557 --> 18:57.759
Listen, anyway, we've
got your wallet, so...

18:57.761 --> 18:59.926
<i>Look, I'd like to give you a reward.</i>

18:59.928 --> 19:01.995
<i>Those photos mean so much to me.</i>

19:01.997 --> 19:04.465
<i>How does $200 sound?</i>

19:04.467 --> 19:06.567
- That's not necessary.
- <i>No, not at all.</i>

19:06.569 --> 19:11.438
It's for your honesty.
It's such a rare quality.

19:11.440 --> 19:14.574
- Hey! Give me the wallet.
- No, I found it.

19:14.576 --> 19:17.844
- Look, I want the wallet.
- Keep the 50. I'm keeping the wallet.

19:17.846 --> 19:20.947
- It's a man's wallet.
- I want it for my dad. You take the money.

19:20.949 --> 19:22.917
The wallet's worth more than $50.

19:22.919 --> 19:25.552
Yes. So?

19:25.554 --> 19:27.487
Take the money?

19:27.489 --> 19:30.824
No, you idiot. What are you doing?

19:30.826 --> 19:32.627
- Please take the money?
- Oh, my God.

19:32.629 --> 19:34.896
(picks up receiver)

19:34.898 --> 19:37.799
He's an idiot.

19:37.801 --> 19:40.501
He wants to talk to you.

19:40.503 --> 19:42.338
Hello?

19:44.774 --> 19:48.342
You're supposed to say, "How
'bout I sell you the wallet?

19:48.344 --> 19:50.610
How much are you willing to pay?"

19:50.612 --> 19:52.679
This is the guy that
busted your chess swindle?

19:52.681 --> 19:57.718
This is Lawrence. He's no Laurence Olivier.

19:57.720 --> 19:59.619
But he is damn cute.

19:59.621 --> 20:02.557
LAWRENCE (narrating): <i>Yeah.
She didn't say that.</i>

20:02.559 --> 20:04.658
(voices rewinding)

20:04.660 --> 20:08.495
- This is the guy that busted your chess swindle?
- This is Lawrence.

20:08.497 --> 20:11.631
I told you that scam was
rubbish. It's old, and so are you.

20:11.633 --> 20:14.136
Lawrence, meet Sarah.

20:17.040 --> 20:20.041
Come on, Dad. We can do better.

20:20.043 --> 20:22.746
We leave tomorrow night.

20:33.823 --> 20:35.689
WOMEN: <i>♪ Don't, don't ♪</i>

20:35.691 --> 20:37.125
<i>♪ Don't, don't ♪</i>

20:37.127 --> 20:39.763
<i>♪ Don't, don't ♪</i>

20:41.831 --> 20:45.099
<i>♪ This ordinary thing ♪</i>

20:45.101 --> 20:49.304
<i>♪ Can be more colorful
than you say it is ♪</i>

20:50.640 --> 20:53.707
<i>♪ The cardinal sin ♪</i>

20:53.709 --> 20:58.678
<i>♪ Is to tell a lie, but
now you must give in ♪</i>

20:58.680 --> 21:00.982
<i>♪ The storm came down on you ♪</i>

21:00.984 --> 21:03.150
<i>♪ Just like it was the end ♪♪</i>

21:03.152 --> 21:05.086
I've never heard of such a thing.

21:05.088 --> 21:07.655
It's like a bus with medical students.

21:07.657 --> 21:10.057
We drive around to help
out country hospitals.

21:10.059 --> 21:12.760
- Medibus.
- But you are not a medical student.

21:12.762 --> 21:15.331
Not yet.

21:16.733 --> 21:20.503
I need a job if I'm ever
going to pay back Dad.

21:22.772 --> 21:25.106
