- How do you know that?

23:08.277 --> 23:10.878
It's an expensive suit.

23:10.880 --> 23:13.747
Cheap shoes.

23:13.749 --> 23:16.684
The affectation of status.

23:16.686 --> 23:18.985
That's his tell.

23:18.987 --> 23:21.187
He's a salesman, popular at school,

23:21.189 --> 23:23.724
probably captain of the football team.

23:23.726 --> 23:26.726
- He's married, but he's having an affair.
- How do you know?

23:26.728 --> 23:29.129
He has a mobile, but
he's using a pay phone.

23:29.131 --> 23:31.232
- His wife checks his bills.
- The battery could be flat.

23:31.234 --> 23:33.269
(chuckles)

23:35.772 --> 23:38.939
I used to have partners.

23:38.941 --> 23:41.676
Long ago, far away.

23:41.678 --> 23:45.846
We pulled long cons,
short cons, card scams.

23:45.848 --> 23:48.349
We played the Melon Drop, the Rainmaker,

23:48.351 --> 23:52.088
the Fiddle Game, the
Wire, and even the Badger.

23:53.156 --> 23:56.657
Always assume that the more
sordid explanation is correct.

23:56.659 --> 23:59.329
