with the weight, the feel,

33:42.911 --> 33:45.378
the size of them.

33:45.380 --> 33:47.246
Like the touch of a lover's breast.

33:47.248 --> 33:49.919
Wax on, wax off.

34:00.528 --> 34:04.764
That's a bezique deck...

34:04.766 --> 34:06.802
from 1910.

34:07.902 --> 34:10.803
All 64 of them.

34:10.804 --> 34:13.505
Cards used to be known as pasteboards.

34:13.507 --> 34:16.210
You just feel the thickness of those.

34:17.545 --> 34:22.547
There's over a hundred
years of grit on them.

34:22.550 --> 34:24.984
It's the most valuable thing that I own.

34:24.985 --> 34:28.521
- What about me?
- I don't own you, my dear.

34:28.523 --> 34:31.225
That much is obvious.

34:31.226 --> 34:34.360
These are beautiful.

34:34.362 --> 34:36.329
Where'd you get them from?

34:36.331 --> 34:38.967
They were a wedding
gift from an old friend.

34:40.568 --> 34:42.902
The only thing from that
friendship that survived.

34:42.905 --> 34:44.771
(chuckles)

34:44.773 --> 34:47.306
